<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,365,1124,1148]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body medium-sized; surace finely pubescent. Head of subequal width with anterior margin of pronotum; eyes slightly bulging and ovoid. Median ocellus round, slightly depressed; lateral ocelli absent. Frontal rostrum slightly narrower than scapus (
<number box="[575,591,1194,1217]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="9.0">9</number>
: 
<number box="[602,632,1194,1217]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="10.0">10</number>
). Pronotum widened posteriorly, anterior margin straight, posterior margin slightly protuberant in middle, lateral margins rounded bent into paranota; lateral lobes semicircular. Metanotal gland developed, anterior half broader than posterior half, internal surface of gland covered with long hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1361,1264,1287]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1079,1103]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,201,1045]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,194,1055]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Noctitrella denticulata sp. nov.: 1. metanotal gland, dorsal view; 2 – 4. phallus (2. dorsal view; 3. ventral view; 4. lateral view); 5. supra anal plate, dorsal view; scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[1349,1361,1264,1287]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), with bulging and elevated margins around central concavity, posterior margin triangularly emarginated in middle. Tegmina distinctly extending over apex of abdomen, with 
<number box="[680,693,1333,1356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="2.0">2</number>
long and 
<number box="[801,814,1333,1356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="5.0">5</number>
short oblique veins; mirror slightly longer than wide (
<number box="[1402,1432,1333,1356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="16.0">16</number>
: 
<number box="[151,180,1368,1391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="10.0">10</number>
); apical area long; lateral area with 
<number box="[580,607,1368,1391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="15.0">15</number>
oblique subcostal veinlets. Fore tibia strongly swollen at tympana; internal tympanum with a slit-like opening on posterior side; external tympanum oblong and free.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Supra anal plate wider than long, triangularly emarginated in middle of posterior margin; areas above cerci respectively by a fold from lateral part of plate (
<figureCitation box="[682,750,1472,1495]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1079,1103]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,201,1045]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,194,1055]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Noctitrella denticulata sp. nov.: 1. metanotal gland, dorsal view; 2 – 4. phallus (2. dorsal view; 3. ventral view; 4. lateral view); 5. supra anal plate, dorsal view; scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[734,750,1472,1495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate strongly swollen at base. Phallus developed (
<figureCitation box="[159,258,1506,1529]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1079,1103]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,201,1045]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,194,1055]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Noctitrella denticulata sp. nov.: 1. metanotal gland, dorsal view; 2 – 4. phallus (2. dorsal view; 3. ventral view; 4. lateral view); 5. supra anal plate, dorsal view; scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Figs. 
<number box="[219,258,1506,1529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2-4</number>
</figureCitation>
): epiphallus vertically reflexed at base, distinctly divided in middle of apex, each side covered with short hairs on a large part of dorsal surface; epiphallus parameres short, multidentated; rami short, each with a projection near apical one-third of outer side; endophallus sclerotized and lamellated, with rounded apex, endophallus apodemes distinctly short; ectophallus parameres short, with rounded apex; ectophallus apodemes distinctly longer than endophallus apodemes, but not reaching apex of rami.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,328,1679,1703]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body brown with black markings. Head and pronotum dark brown, first two joint of antennae yellow. Tegmina brown, with black brown markings at basal and apical areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,2015]" box="[197,406,1748,1772]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,287,1748,1772]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,2015]" box="[197,1371,1783,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,439,1783,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male: body 
<number box="[574,603,1784,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="17.0">17</number>
.0, length with wings 22.5, pronotum 4.2, tegmen 
<number box="[1134,1163,1784,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="18.0">18</number>
.0, hind femur 11.3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
