<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1852,1876]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov" authorityName="Gorochov" box="[637,889,1853,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Noctitrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tranquilla">
<emphasis box="[637,775,1853,1876]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">N. tranquilla</emphasis>
Gorochov
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the dorsal area of head and pronotum uniform coloration, without markings; epiphallus parameres short, multidentated; rami each with a projection near apical one-third of outer side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,333,1956,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from Latin words “ 
<taxonomicName box="[902,1031,1957,1980]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Noctitrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denticulata">
<emphasis box="[902,1031,1957,1980]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">denticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (dentate), referring to the apex of epiphallus parameres multidentated.
</paragraph>
